Purpose: Define versioning for models, scoring rules, and research outputs.

Scope

Dossier versioning

Scoring model/rules versioning (semver)

Dataset schema versioning

Backtesting snapshots

Deprecation windows for old scoring versions

Outputs

Version policy

Upgrade and rollback strategy

NS-PIE-007 — DATAMODEL

Purpose: Define the canonical data model for PIE.

Scope

ProductCandidate

Listing/Offer

Market/Channel

Vendor/Supplier/3PL

SignalRecord (typed)

FeatureVector (derived)

ScoreCard (outputs + confidence)

Dossier (narrative + citations)

Recommendation (action proposal) + EvidenceRefs

Outputs

Entity definitions + required fields

Correlation requirements (workflow_id, decision_id, integration_id)

NS-PIE-008 — EEE (End-to-End Example)

Purpose: Provide a full scenario showing PIE producing actionable outcomes.

Scope (example scenario)

Discover product candidates via SIG/DRE

Enrich with pricing, reviews, and supplier shortlist via MUX

Compute margin + demand proxy score

Route to CWP for human review + vendor outreach tasks

If approved, hand off to FLO (sample purchase) and SIM (scenario modeling)

LUM correlates the end-to-end workflow

Outputs

Sequence diagram

Happy path + failure path (data source unavailable, low confidence, policy blocked)

