Compliance incidents (source restrictions)

Outputs

Playbooks by incident type

Escalation guidance and comms templates

NS-PIE-014 — DATADEF

Purpose: Field-level definitions, enums, validation, and redaction rules.

Scope

Candidate and listing fields

Signal and feature definitions

Score definitions and confidence fields

Citation/source attribution fields

Redaction rules (never store secrets; handle personal data carefully)

High-cardinality constraints for labels/metrics

Outputs

Canonical field dictionary

Validation constraints + “never store” list

Notes on Alignment

PIE uses MUX for external provider calls and must not embed provider secrets.

PIE routes operational actions into CWP (tasks) rather than acting directly.

Any spending decisions or payments flow through FLO, governed by GGP.

PIE’s analysis is observable via LUM and should always emit correlation IDs.

PIE may consume signals from SIG and deep research outputs from DRE, but PIE is responsible for product-level normalization, scoring, and recommendations.

